2005-06-20 19:15  cyberhorse

	* db/upgrade_latest.sql, modules/tasks/tree.js: Together with the
	previous change - part of the ajax tasks list change

2005-06-20 19:07  cyberhorse

	* db/dotproject.sql, modules/tasks/listtasks.php,
	modules/tasks/tasks.class.php, modules/tasks/tasks.php: New method
	to expand/collapse tasks (using ajax) This is configurable in the
	configuration (setting tasks_ajax_list), so the old behaviour is
	still available if required.  The new behaviour is that when the
	plus is clicked, tasks are loaded from the server through XMLHTTP
	and added to the table. Consequent requests use javascript
	visibility to hide/unhide rows, so in effect speeds up collapsable
	tasks operations by a lot (imho).
	
	That was a fairly big change with a lot of nasty js, so it is
	likely to have bugs - please report them as soon as you find them!
	:)

